Document: UDPServer
Path: godot/classes/class_udpserver.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for the UDPServer class in Godot Engine.

Method: get_local_port() → int
Returns the local port the server is listening on.

Method: is_connection_available() → bool
Returns true if there is an incoming packet waiting.

Method: is_listening() → bool
Returns true if the server is currently listening for connections.

Method: listen(port: int, bind_address: String = "*") → Error
Starts listening on the given port and optionally on the specified bind address. Returns an Error code.

Method: poll() → Error
Checks for incoming packets and updates the server's state. Returns an Error code.

Method: stop() → void
Stops the server from listening.

Method: take_connection() → PacketPeerUDP
Accepts a new incoming connection and returns it as a PacketPeerUDP.
---CHUNK---
Document: UDPServer
Path: godot/classes/class_udpserver.rst
Summary: Configures the maximum number of pending connections for the UDPServer.

Property: max_pending_connections (int)
Description: Define the maximum number of pending connections, during poll, any new pending connection exceeding that value will be automatically dropped. Setting this value to 0 effectively prevents any new pending connection to be accepted (e.g. when all your players have connected).
Default: 16
Setter: set_max_pending_connections(value: int)
Getter: get_max_pending_connections() -> int
